<TITLE> Clouds may clear Friday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 19 (bdnews24.com)  The weather is likely to start clearing from Friday afternoon, the Meteorological Department said in a forecast Thursday. The steep pressure gradient, bringing a moderate-to-strong monsoon over the north Bay of Bengal and coastal areas of the country, would continue until then, said the weather office. The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla were still advised to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number three until further notice. All fishing boats and trawlers in the north Bay have been also been advised to remain close to the coast and proceed with caution till further notice. bdn
